                    src="assets/Screenshot (69).png",
                    width=384,
                    height=245,
                    fit=ft.ImageFit.COVER
                ),
                ft.Text(
                    "The ICDS is one of the largest and most significant child welfare programs in India. Launched in 1975, it aims to improve the nutritional and health status of children under 6 years of age, pregnant women, and lactating mothers. The program focuses on early childhood care and development, including health, education, and nutrition services.By focusing on the health, nutrition, and education of children and the well-being of pregnant women and lactating mothers, it plays a crucial role in improving the overall health and development of the population, particularly in rural and underserved areas.",
